message.content:
cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the problem of multiplayer QoE fairness in internet video delivery systems, which involves network protocols and architectures. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with adaptive video streaming, which is a multimedia application. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a non-linear MPC-based, router-assisted bandwidth allocation algorithm that regards each player as closed-loop systems, which involves control theory and system design. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of client-side bitrate adaptation algorithms to maximize single-player QoE, which involves information theory and coding. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper addresses the efficiency and fairness of multiplayer HTTP-based adaptive video streaming, which involves performance evaluation and optimization.
